Loiter behavior has improved dramatically.

The aircraft now:
- performs stable sustained orbiting
- uses moderate control surfaces
- avoids rudder saturation
- exhibits smoother guidance behavior

However, coordinated-turn realism still incomplete.

============================================================
CURRENT MAIN ISSUE
============================================================

Telemetry shows:
REQ_BANK ≈ 20°
actual BANK ≈ 2°

Yet aircraft still turns significantly.

This indicates:
turn dynamics still insufficiently tied to bank angle.

The aircraft still partially "cheats" the turn.

============================================================
REQUIRED IMPROVEMENTS
============================================================

1. Strengthen bank-to-turn coupling.

Turning should arise primarily from:
tilted lift vector.

Not:
yaw steering.

============================================================
2. Reduce residual yaw steering authority further.
============================================================

Yaw should:
- coordinate turn
- damp sideslip

NOT:
generate substantial turn curvature.

============================================================
3. Improve lateral acceleration model.
============================================================

Bank angle should directly influence:
centripetal acceleration.

============================================================
4. Increase realism of coordinated-turn dynamics.
============================================================

Proper turn relation:
turn_rate ≈ g * tan(bank) / airspeed

Use this relationship explicitly.

============================================================
5. Add bank tracking reward.
============================================================

Reward matching:
actual_bank ↔ required_bank

============================================================
6. Penalize turning with insufficient bank.
============================================================

If:
turn_rate high
AND bank low

apply penalty.

============================================================
7. Improve orbit acquisition logic.
============================================================

Current loiter still occasionally diverges during orbit capture.

Use:
- smoother intercept trajectory
- predictive tangential capture
- lower aggressiveness near target radius

============================================================
8. Raise target loiter cruise speed.
============================================================

Current loiter speed still low.

Target:
13–16 m/s.

Reduce:
high-AoA low-energy orbiting.

============================================================
9. Add telemetry validation.
============================================================

Current telemetry appears partially inconsistent:
trajectory curvature vs reported turn rate.

Validate:
- turn-rate computation
- heading derivative
- lateral acceleration telemetry

============================================================
10. PPO telemetry still broken.
============================================================

Fix PPO metrics panel:
- policy loss
- value loss
- KL
- entropy